mpted by trump's recent comments that putin has been "far more" of a leader than obama. overall, 60% chose obama, while 23% said putin -- but a plurality (39%) of republicans chose putin, with about a quarter saying they "don't know." the elon university poll of north carolina surveyed 644 likely voters, with a margin of error of +/- 3.86 points. it was conducted from september 12-16.       poll: trump and clinton deadlocked in north carolina      
